title: Total neutron cross sections of lanthanum and praseodymium in the energy range from 20 to 240 keV

x4freetext: Total neutron cross sections of lanthanum and
praseodymium in the energy range from 20 to 240 keV
LiF (5 mm diam.) evaporated on to Mo backing
Neutrons collimated by a polyethylene collimator in
the direction of 100+/-1.8 deg with respect to proton
20.5 cm in effective length, 96% enriched 10BF3 gas
of 500 Torr.) arranged in ring geometry.
The reliability of the detector-system was checked by
the measurement of the total neutron cross-sections
of carbon in the energy range of 10 to 250 keV.
COMMENT changed, La and Pr x-sect.
replaced by new version, C data remain.
A.P.T. Japan code changed to JPN
